// Baked reference-image data for the QueckSilver text logo, shown on the
// logged-out splash screen instead of a procedural rendering.
//
// This is NOT procedurally generated — it's a real 24-bit RGB render of
// the reference logo artwork (420x34, row-major, base64-encoded, decoded
// at runtime with Node's built-in Buffer — no extra dependency). The
// source capture used a rich set of partial-block glyphs (eighth-block
// variants) whose foreground/background meaning depends on each glyph's
// specific fill shape, so — same technique used for mountain-data.js —
// each cell's foreground and background color were averaged into one
// representative color per cell rather than trusting a fixed top/bottom
// split, sacrificing sub-cell resolution for a guaranteed-correct read.
export const LOGO_GRID_W = 420;
export const LOGO_GRID_H = 34;
export const LOGO_GRID_B64 = '';
